Description: Ostracon, section (broken into four pieces) of the body of a dark red-brown pottery vessel, the fabric is partially grey in section, the exterior is covered with a red-brown slip and remains of at least four lines of black-painted demotic text.
Dimensions: Height: 4.90 centimetres (max;fragment marked with Big Number)
Width: 5.90 centimetres (max;fragment marked with Big Number)
Curator's comments: Being studied for publication by Bryan Kraemer. Cemeteries and Osireion Excavations Group
Bibliographic references: Frankfort 1933 / The Cenotaph of Seti I at Abydos (no.?,p.95)
